# `features/` (and sparse `components/tools`)

## `features/`

Use for **cross-surface domain slices**: the same substantive UI/logic must be composed from **more than one app surface**—typically **`app/(main)/.../page.tsx` plus **`GeneratedUILayout`** from **`components/assistant/generated-ui-layout.tsx`**.

- **One folder per slice** under **`features/<name>/`**: domain UI (**`features/pantry/pantry-list.tsx`**, …). **`"use server"`** handlers live under **`lib/actions/<slice>.ts`** (e.g. **`lib/actions/pantry.ts`**), imported by the feature client module.
- **Imports**: route **`page.tsx`** and **`components/assistant/generated-ui-layout.tsx`** compose **`@/features/...`**; keep substantive domain UI in **`features/`**.

## `components/tools`

**`components/tools`:** reserve for assistant-adjacent UI that stays **outside** **`app/`** (rare once route colocation covers preview shells).

**Assistant preview shell** is **`components/assistant/generated-ui-layout.tsx`** (used from **`app/(main)/assistant/page.tsx`**); it composes **`features/`** slices—not primary **`/routes`** domain markup that ships without the assistant surface.
